H0.text: Who was the first emperor of Rome. Julius Caesar

H1.text: Who was the first emperor of Rome. Romulus

H2.text: Who was the first emperor of Rome. Lucius Cornelius Sulla

H3.text: Who was the first emperor of Rome. Agustus

A4.text: The Roman emperors were the rulers of the Roman Empire from the granting of the name and title Augustus to Octavian by the Roman Senate in 27 BC onward.

A5.text: The title of Augustus was conferred on his successors to the imperial position, and emperors gradually grew more monarchical and authoritarian.
